        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 8:45PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 845 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Pendergrass, or near
Jefferson, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Jefferson, Braselton, Arcade, Hoschton, Pendergrass, Talmo, and Peach
State Speedway.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
